data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` instead of casting manually. It's cleaner and gives a better failure message:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(factory.Create("email"));

    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

The generic overload returns the cast value, so you can use `handler` directly for further assertions — no manual cast or null check needed.
